We refer to an online article on the factors affecting glomerular filtration rate (GFR). Net filtration pressure (NFP) is calculated as the difference between the hydrostatic pressure in the glomerular capillary (PGC) and the sum of the oncotic pressure in the glomerular capillary (πGC) and the hydrostatic pressure in Bowman’s space (PBS). NFP = PGC - (πGC + PBS). Using the values provided in the question, NFP = 48 - (23 + 10 + 0) = 15 mm Hg. Therefore, the best measure of net filtration pressure in this participant is (A) 15 mm Hg.
